                                        <h1 class="title">Quality - Durability - Performance</h1>
                                <div id="node-2" class="node node-page">
      <div class="content"><p>Applied Motion Systems designs and manufactures motion control systems and specialty machinery for a broad range of commercial and industrial applications. <span style="text-align: center;float:right;margin-left:10px;margin-top:18px"><iframe height="310" width="408" src="/sg20/ams2.html" style="border: 0px none ;"></iframe></span>Relentlessly reliable, our scalable automation solutions withstand harsh factory conditions while delivering excellent production rates.</p>
<p>Our machine retrofit packages improve the performance and flexibility of existing equipment at a fraction of the cost of a new machine.</p>
<p>AMS's automated systems inspect wafers, package printers, machine aerospace components, form wine bottles and much much more.</p>
<p><b>What can we do for you?</b></p>
<ul>
<li>To learn more about our factory automation solutions, <a href="/welcome/coreexpertise">click here</a>.</li>
<li>To discuss your automation project with an experienced systems engineer, <a href="/contact">click here</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<hr>
<br />
<img src="http://www.appliedmotionsystems.com/files/Breaking.jpg" width="200 px" /><br />
</p>
<p><img src="/files/Gambini-AMS Logo.png" width="400px" /></p>
<p><img height="120px" style="float:left" src="/files/Gambini-AMS CoreMaker Winder-Inset.jpg"  />Applied Motion Systems, Inc. (AMS) and <a href="http://www.gambinispa.it" target="_blank">Gambini S.p.A.</a> have signed a joint collaboration agreement to provide Tissue Converting Technology and Engineering Services to the North American marketplace.</p>
<p><img height="140px" style="float:right" src="/files/Gambini-AMS_Coremaker_Web.jpg" />Gambini S.p.A., headquartered in Lucca, Italy, specializes in the manufacture of tissue converting machinery for both the Consumer Retail Market of bathroom tissue and kitchen towel products, and for the “Away-from-Home” Commercial and Industrial roll markets.</p>
<p>“Collaboration with Gambini allows AMS to further help customers increase production throughput and flexibility when upgrading a converting line. Our customers can strategically integrate new Gambini machine sections into their existing production line to address their specific needs and budget,” states Paul Johnson, COO of AMS.</p>
<p>&lt;<a href="http://www.appliedmotionsystems.com/content/gambini_spa_applied_motion_systems_sign_joint_agreement">MORE</a>&gt;</p>
</div>
